Package: pubmedRecords
Type: Package
Title: Get and format NCBI PubMed records and their associated bibliometric data as tidy data
Version: 0.1.1
Date: 2019-08-19
Author: Peter Kamerman <peter.kamerman@gmail.com>
Maintainer: Peter Kamerman <peter.kamerman@gmail.com>
URL: https://github.com/kamermanpr/pubmedRecords
BugReports: https://github.com/kamermanpr/pubmedRecords/issues
Description: This package provides tools to download records from the NCBI PubMed database based on user-specified search criteria, and to add CrossRef citation data for the returned records. The output is in tidy data format, facilitating downstream analysis using tools from the 'tidyverse'. 
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 6.1.1
Depends: 
	R (>= 3.3.3),
Imports:
        dplyr,
	ggthemes,
	magrittr,
	purrr,
	rcrossref,
	stringr,
	tibble,
	tidytext,
	tidyr,
	wordcloud2,
	xml2
Suggests: 
    knitr,
    rmarkdown
VignetteBuilder: knitr
